title: Comfortable, Breathable, Fits Large Faces, Not See-Through When Being Worn
text: This mask is great. Normally I wear disposable masks since they are more hygienic, but I needed something that I could wear during vigorous exercise and in hot environments and this is perfect. The ear loops are thick so they do not hurt the back of my ears like so many other masks. The mask is large so when I talk it does not slip down my face and expose my nose (note I am a male with a fairly large head.) My only concern was that it was going to be transparent like a pair of pantyhose and look fake, but it does not. It looks like a normal cloth mask. Holding it up in the air yes it allows light through, but when being worn it does not and the looseness makes it look thicker than it really is. Best thing is people can actually hear what I am saying 6 ft away, through the mask, and through a plexiglass window. Only downfall is that the mask is pricy for what it is, but at least prime shipping helps. I would not trust this in the washing machine if you want it to last, I will hand-wash it. Even though I am vaxxed, boosted, tested, etc. there are times when I am forced to wear a mask as the state and certain places randomly impose mask mandates.

title: I'm not sure what is nicer, the necklace or the packaging!
text:
[[VIDEOID:b3f59105b97693aba15156fe1e9ab1b9]] This sterling silver Moissanite necklace is well crafted, it has a 1CT main stone and a double heart design. The necklace is beautiful to look at and the Moissanite certainly sparkles in all the colors of the rainbow. When looking at the necklace from back to front I did notice a few parts that didn't have the high polish, like around the barrel that holds the main stone but it's not noticeable unless looking up-close. I would say the necklace is 4 stars in my opinion due to the unpolished spots. When thinking about the necklace and the overall presentation with the leatherette box and heart shaped piano lacquered walnut jewelry box, I would say the overall presentation brings this necklace and it's giftability up-to 5 stars.

The necklace is nice, but I think the piano lacquered walnut jewelry box really brings the whole presentation up a notch. The jewelry box even has a heart shaped mirror inside which is a nice touch. The leatherette box that holds the jewelry box is also well crafted. Inside of the leatherette box you will find the walnut jewelry box that holds the necklace and also a cardboard box that has a jewelry polishing, two heart shaped gifting paper gifting cards, product warranty card against any defects for a year and a GRA card that certifies the authenticity of the Moissanite stone.

Overall beautiful necklace and well crafted jewelry box. I would say this is a highly giftable necklace and suggest using the heart shaped paper cutouts to write a nice note to whoever the special person might be.

title: which was a nice ring but the star sapphire in it was terrible
text:
I bought the TSNjewelry Genuine Blue Star Sapphire Sterling Silver Ring with Diamond Accents, which was a nice ring but the star sapphire in it was terrible. I was going to send it back but realized getting a new one was just as much of a crap shoot in regards to the quality of the star sapphire and that I might want to just replace the gem itself, which I did. The customer support did say they would be happy to allow me to send it back but claimed the one I got was, "exactly as the picture showed" which it was not. The gem I was sent was flat and not domed like the pictured showed. This made a big difference in the look of the ring and star showing up in light and the location of the star was way off center. To make the star look center the ring had to be tilted so about 70 degrees from the eye which made it hard to see very well at all. If you know anything about the star sapphire you know that its all about quality. The gems range in value from $5 to $50,000 and the difference between a $10,000 gem and a $20 gem isn't always noticeable to an on looker at all. The really good ones sparkle in even dim lighting, the bad ones need to be directly under a clear skied sun. Also the sharpness and strait lines in the star are a sign of quality, wavy lines happen in most gems but how wavy is key. The depth of the star in a good one seems almost impossibly floating inside the gem also making for a great quality. The shape and size of the gem too, and more. I was able to easily bend the mounting tines out and the sizing of the gem I ordered a 1.57-2.12 Cts 8x6 mm Oval Sapphire Loose Gemstone that was exactly as described and it fit perfectly in the setting and turned an unremarkable ring into something people are now asking about quite a bit.
You can see in the pictures the TSN gem is much more flat, has a star that is way off center and, you can't tell as much in the pictures but it doesn't show up at al in dimmer light and the lines are blurry and . I bought that box with the light in it to highlight the star in the sapphire, it did not come with the ring or loose gem. The silver ring itself was very nice, I don't really know enough about diamond to speak about them and the star sapphire was terrible.

title: I chose this one because it worked for putting the building name
text:
I needed a personalized welcome mat that showed the name of the building being entered, not the name of a family that owned the house or lived in a house, so of the dozens of personalized mats I looked at, this is the only one that allowed for that, that didn't say something along the lines of "Welcome to the Hendersons'."

As for durability and longevity, since I only got it today, I can't really speak to that. What I can say is it SEEMS it'll be highly durable and have longevity. I've owned coir welcome mats before, and they are very durable and long-lasting, and this seems as good as any coir mat I've owned. In past coir mats I've had, I've found colors applied to the coir tend to fade, all colors except black with white fading completely away, so by the only color applied to this mat being black, I expect it'll stay new-looking a very long time.

Oh, and another thing I like about this mat is its SIZE. Very few mats, including very few personalized mats, come in a 36" width, which is odd since a standard entry door is 36" wide, so if you buy a mat that's smaller than 36", most often only 32" wide (the standard width of an interior door, not an entry door) or even sometimes only 28" wide, you end up with a mat that looks too small for the door you've placed it in front of. It boggles my mind why the vast majority of welcome mats are made too small for a standard entry door, but whatever the why, that's the case, and a MAJOR BENEFIT of this product is it's NOT TOO SMALL for a standard entry door but EXACTLY THE SAME WIDTH-- 36 inches.
